# Cloudflare Pages routing for moavoca.com
#
# CF Pages auto-resolves .html extensions, so most static routes work
# without a rule (e.g. /app/library → dist/app/library.html). Only
# DYNAMIC routes need explicit fallback to their [param].html exports.
#
# CF Pages _redirects gotchas (learned during deploy):
#   - 404 is NOT a valid status code. Allowed: 200, 301-303, 307-308.
#   - A broad rewrite rule like `/app/* /app/index.html 200` is rejected
#     as an "infinite loop". Narrow patterns to specific subpaths so the
#     destination never matches the source.
#
# Order matters — most specific first.

# SPA mode (app.json web.output = "single"): expo emits a single
# /app/index.html shell and the router does all path matching client-side.
# CF Pages serves real static files first (e.g. /app/_expo/static/js/...),
# falling back to this rewrite only for paths that have no file on disk —
# which is exactly the SPA routes we want to land in the shell.
/app/*  /app/index.html  200
